# macOS
.DS_Store

# Typst build output (target/ used by tooling like Makefiles)
target/

# Generated example outputs.
# - `examples/*.pdf` covers every top-level demo render (example.pdf
#   and any future `examples/*.typ` demo). CI rebuilds them on every
#   push and attaches them as workflow artifacts + release assets,
#   so they stay out of git to avoid binary churn. The `*` glob is
#   single-segment, so per-fixture PDFs under `examples/tests/` are
#   NOT matched and stay tracked (see below).
# - `examples/example_full.pdf` is the explicit exception — tracked
#   so the README's Gallery link resolves via raw.githubusercontent
#   without a local rebuild (same pattern as cv.png). The
#   negation must come AFTER the broader `examples/*.pdf` line.
# - `examples/tests/*.pdf` is tracked (not listed here) — one
#   rendered PDF per `tests/*.typ` fixture as a visible reference
#   for each permutation of the template's output.
# - `examples/cv.png`, `examples/preview.gif`, and the per-page
#   gallery PNGs (`examples/example_full-*.png`) are tracked
#   (not listed here) so the README images resolve immediately on
#   GitHub and Typst Universe without needing a local rebuild.
examples/*.pdf
!examples/example_full.pdf
examples/*.pdf.tmp
examples/preview-*.png

# Sed-swap temp sources created by `make cv` / `make thumbnail`.
# Recipes `rm -f` them on success, but a compile failure (or Ctrl-C)
# can leave one behind — ignoring keeps `git add -A` clean.
.cv-pdf-src.typ
.cv-png-src.typ
.thumbnail-src.typ
.thumbnail-*.png

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
out/
*.swp
